.\" ── BUGS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
Remote-tracking branches (e.g.\&
.BR origin/feature/foo )
produce detached HEAD worktrees.
Create a local tracking branch first:
.EX
git checkout \-b feature/foo origin/feature/foo
wt add feature/foo
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Branch sanitization is one-way: two distinct branches can map to the
same directory name (e.g.\&
.B a/b
and
.BR a\-b ).
.B wt add
will fail on the second with a "directory already exists" error.
.IP \(bu 2
.B export \-f wt
in
.B \*[WT_INIT]
exports the function to bash subshells only; zsh does not inherit
exported shell functions.
